# Implementation Plan - Order Editing Functionality

Allowing users to modify active (non-completed) orders directly from the Orders Panel.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Editing an order will load it back into the POS cart. Any existing items in your current cart will be replaced. 
> The system will handle stock restoration for removed items and deduction for new items during the update process.

## Proposed Changes

### [Sales Module]

#### [MODIFY] [SalesService.js](file:///home/muawiaimtiaz/code-drive/rms-system-v-online/services/SalesService.js)
*   Implement `updateSaleItems(saleId, newItems, shopId)`:
    *   Fetch previous items.
    *   Restore stock for previous items (Raw stock or Product batches).
    *   Delete old items.
    *   Register new items and deduct stock (using existing `createSale` logic where possible).
    *   Recalculate total.

#### [MODIFY] [sales.js](file:///home/muawiaimtiaz/code-drive/rms-system-v-online/routes/sales.js)
*   Add `PUT /api/sales/:id/items` route to handle the item update request.

### [POS Frontend]

#### [MODIFY] [app.js](file:///home/muawiaimtiaz/code-drive/rms-system-v-online/public/js/app.js)
*   **Global State**: Add `_editingOrderId = null;`.
*   **order Editing**:
    *   Update `renderPOSOrders` to include an "Edit" button.
    *   Implement `editOrder(id)`:
        *   Fetch order details.
        *   Populate the `cart` with order items.
        *   Set `_editingOrderId = id`.
        *   Switch UI to the POS panel.
        *   Trigger `updateCartUI()`.
*   **Cart UI**:
    *   If `_editingOrderId` is set, change the checkout button text to "Update Order" and color it (e.g., Amber).
    *   Add a "Cancel Edit" button to return to normal POS mode.
*   **Checkout Logic**:
    *   Modify `checkout()` to check if `_editingOrderId` is set.
    *   If editing, call `PUT /api/sales/:id/items` instead of the normal `POST /api/sales`.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
*   Create an order with 2 Pizzas.
*   Edit order -> Change to 1 Pizza and 1 Drink.
*   Verify stock of Pizza is restored by 1 and Drink is deducted by 1.
*   Verify sale total is updated.

### Manual Verification
1.  Create a "Kitchen" order.
2.  Go to Orders Panel.
3.  Click "Edit" on that order.
4.  Verify POS loads with those items.
5.  Add/Remove items.
6.  Click "Update Order".
7.  Verify the order is updated in the list.
